@database UNRTF
@master "UNRTF."GNU"
@remark "manual page source format generated by PolyglotMan v3.2 available at http://polyglotman.sourceforge.net/"
@wordwrap
@tab 8

@node sect0 "Name"
UnRTF - converts document in RTF format to other formats 
@endnode

@node sect1 "Synopsis"
@{b}unrtf [@{ub}@{i}options@{ui}@{b}] [@{ub}@{i}file...@{ui}@{b}]@{ub} 
Options:  @{b}[--nopict]@{ub} @{b}[--noremap]@{ub} @{b}[--html]@{ub} @{b}[--text]@{ub} @{b}[--vt]@{ub} @{b}[--latex]@{ub} @{b}[--help]@{ub} @{b}[--verbose]@{ub} @{b}[--version]@{ub} 

@endnode

@node sect2 "Description"
The program @{b}unrtf@{ub} is a converter from Rich Text Format (RTF) to a growing number of document formats. At present it supports Hypertext Markup Language (HTML), plain text, text with VT100 codes, and LaTeX . All output formats except HTML are "alpha" i.e. limited and development has just begun. However with HTML, the program supports tables, fonts,  hyperlinks, and paragraph alignment. Font support includes face and size changes, as well as  typical attributes such as italic, bold,  underlining, strikethrough, smallcaps, allcaps, expand, compress and both foreground and background colors. Images are always stored to separate files in the current directory, or they can be ignored. 
@endnode

@node sect3 "Options"


· --nopict  @{lindent 3}
disables the automatic storing of embedded pictures to the current directory. @{lindent 0}

· --noremap @{lindent 3}
disables charset conversion (currently only works for 8-bit charsets). @{lindent 0}

· --html @{lindent 3}
selects HTML output (default). @{lindent 0}

· --text @{lindent 3}
selects plain ASCII text output. @{lindent 0}

· --vt @{lindent 3}
selects text output with VT100 escape codes. @{lindent 0}

· --latex @{lindent 3}
selects output of a LaTeX document. @{lindent 0}

· --verbose  @{lindent 3}
prints additional information. @{lindent 0}

· --version  @{lindent 3}
prints the program version. @{lindent 0}


@endnode

@node sect4 "Website"
http://www.gnu.org/software/unrtf/unrtf.html 
@endnode

@node sect5 "Notes"
Report bugs in the program to daved@physiol.usyd.edu.au 
@endnode
